  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160401T103300+0300" comment="The 4 template types need to have their own topics."?>WebHelp
    Responsive Template Pages<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <body>
    <p>The HTML pages that compose a WebHelp Responsive output are obtained after processing the
      HTML template pages.</p>
    <p>Depending on their function, there are four types of template pages:</p>
    <ol id="ol_bjw_znf_mv">
      <li><b>Main page template</b> used to produce the home page of the WebHelp Responsive
        output.</li>
      <li><b>Topic template</b> used to generate the HTML pages associated with a topic.</li>
      <li><b><?oxy_comment_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160407T091013+0300" comment="Is it Search Result Template?"?>Search
          template<?oxy_comment_end?></b> used to generate the HTML page that presents the search
        results.</li>
      <li><b>Index terms template</b> used when generating the HTML page that presents the
        documentation index terms.</li>
    </ol>
    <section id="section_wh_main_page_template">
      <title>WebHelp Main Page Template</title>
      <p>This template is used to generate the home page of the WebHelp Responsive output.</p>
      <p>The main function of the home page is to display links that help you easily reach any of
        the top level topics of the publication. These links can be rendered either in a
          <term>tile</term> or <term>tree</term>-like layout. </p>
    </section>
